name: FLUKE FANZINE #11
description: Interviews with buZ blurr (Colossus of Roads moniker!), Ed Crawford (fIREHOSE, FOOD), Negative Approach, Barker Gee (Neon Piss, Wet Spots) + Bad Years! Writings by Mark Howe + Bert Burroughs. Comic by Everett Gee. Awesome! 40 pages, half-size, offset print.

name: FLUKE FANZINE #10
description:
Interviews w/Burt Taggart (Chino Horde, Big Cats, Max Recordings), Emily's Army, Mystic Knights of the Cobra, Anna Joy Springer (Blatz, author of "The Vicious Red Relic"), Alex the Russian (w/cameo by Angel Nova of The Phenomenauts). Writings by Steve Davis (bassist of Phoenix punk band Glass Heroes) and Janie January (of Seattle's The Januariez). Eisner Award Winner Nate Powell illustrated the variant cover!
32 pages, half-size, offset print.

name: FLUKE FANZINE #9
description:
This issue marks the 20th anniversary of fluke! #9 has interviews with co-founders STEVE SCHMIDT and JASON WHITE, as well as the bands BOBBY JOE EBOLA AND THE CHILDREN MACNUGGITS and THE BODY. There's also an all-day playlist by MITCHELL CRISP, tour tips by MIKE SCOTT, a comic by BRIAN MADDEN and "BULLSHIT WOLF" by MICHAEL FOURNIER. Cover art by BOBBY MATTHEWS!

56 pages, half-size, offset print.

name: FLUKE FANZINE #8
description:
Fluke #8 has interviews with Christ on Parade, Andrew Jackson Jihad, Paige Hearn and Alan Short. Writings by Shane Halvorson, Tre Baker and Mark "Sledge" Howe. 

64 pages, half-size, offset print.

name: FLUKE FANZINE #7
description:
Fluke #7 has interviews with Mike Watt (Minutemen, fIREHOSE, Mike Watt + The Missingmen, etc), Kevin Kerby and Mark "Sledge" Howe. Writings by Andrew D'Arezzo, Shane Halvorson and Stevie D. Cover art by Nate Powell!

40 pages, half-size, offset print.
